<section id="section-1b">
<title> Velocity of the point object  </title>

<para id="element-12">We can obtain velocity of the object by differentiating its position with respect to time. As the measurements of position in two references are different, it is expected that velocities in two references are different, because one observer is at rest, whereas other observer is moving with constant velocity. 
</para>
