<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> - </m:mo>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>

<para id="element-54">
Let us consider that the direction 
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
is the positive reference direction.
</para>
<para id="element-55">
Here, 
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
= 1 m/s  and 
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
= -2 m/s. Thus, relative velocity of two cars (of 2 w.r.t 1) is :
</para>



<para id="element-52">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mo> ⇒ </m:mo> 
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
