<m:mi> s </m:mi>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>



<para id="element-56">This means that car "2" is approaching car "1" with a speed of -3 m/s along the straight road. Similarly, car "1" is approaching car "2" with a speed of 3 m/s along the straight road. Therefore, we can say that two cars are approaching at a speed of 3 m/s. Now, let the two cars meet after time “t” :
</para>
